  "instructions": [
    {
      "step": 1,
      "text": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped onion</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1737454596392-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 2,
      "text": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and<strong> saffron </strong>in 750ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[975ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.4L] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1737454599680-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 3,
      "text": "<p>Once the onion is beginning to soften, add your<strong> arborio rice</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add your <strong>white wine vinegar</strong> and cook for a further 30 secs or until it has evaporated, then reduce the heat to medium-low</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1737454606183-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 4,
      "text": "<p>Add the<strong> vegetable</strong> <strong>stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for 25-30 min or until all of the stock is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1737454614977-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 5,
      "text": "<p>Whilst the risotto is cooking, roll your<strong> lemon[s] </strong>with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice) and cut in half</p><p>Grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Wash your<strong> salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1737454634005-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 6,
      "text": "<p>When the risotto is almost cooked, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>sea bass fillet[s]</strong> skin dry with kitchen paper and season with a pinch with <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>once hot, add your <strong>sea bass fillet[s]</strong>, skin side down and cook for 6 min, then flip the sea bass and cook for 1 min further or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1737454638423-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 7,
      "text": "<p>Once your risotto has absorbed all the stock, remove the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>risotto </strong>from the heat and stir in the <strong>grated</strong> <strong>cheddar cheese</strong> and a generous knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Add the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lemon[s]</strong></p><p>Season very generously with <strong>pepper </strong>and give everything a good mix up â€“ this is your <strong>lemon and saffron risotto</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the risotto is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "imageUrl": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1737454641734-x200.jpg"
    },
    {
      "step": 8,
      "text": "<p>Serve the <strong>lemon and saffron risotto</strong> topped with a handful of<strong> salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle the<strong> salad</strong> with a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>sea bass</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>"
    }
